Well a few weeks ago I decided to do something for myself that was bothering me over the past few years. My nose..!!! I was getting more and more conscious of the uneven split cartilage and the angle of my nose pointing down especially when I would smile, it had been getting worse over the years. So I met with an incredible cosmetic surgeon, I had seen and researched his work and was super impressed by  @butlerfacialplasticsurgery who fully understood and explained to me the way he could help fix my nose issues medically and cosmetically. Dr David Butler helped with breathing and the aesthetic of my concerns. It was a very quick and painless procedure I couldn’t believe how efficient and quick it was - I’m very happy with the subtlety yet effectiveness of the results of his work. So grateful and enjoying it more and more each day. Thank you again @butlerfacialplasticsurgery and all the staff you made this an easy and enjoyable experience. 
I have shared some before pics as well so you can see … 
#justthetip

Happy birthday to the man that makes me wanna turn 50 @james_marsden one of the best - I can’t put into words on a post the good times and epic life experiences so here is a look back at some of the memories to hopefully make ya smile Im very grateful our worlds collided 🙏🏼

So thankful to be invited to #avedacongress What an incredible day filled with so much creativity and brilliance in one room. I was totally inspired by all the amazing artists. It was so lovely to be back in person for a hair show to see all the new innovations of the @aveda brand first hand and how each artist had their very own take on color, cut, braiding and texture. Aveda is so passionate about Clean Beauty and where they source all their ingredients (they all smell amazing). I really got to dive in and learn more about the brand and how they blend the perfect ingredients to create such great lines of product. Thank you again for an amazing weekend. I look forward to many more! #avedapartner

Giving that effortless undone voluminous blowout using @verbproducts #styledwithverb #ad thanks you @leahhaywood for being my beautiful hair model and the epic track 🎶 

	1.	Start with Verb’s Bonding Shampoo and Mask. I always like to do 2 shampoos followed by a conditioner or mask. 
	2.	Spray Verb’s Volume Spray at the roots on damp hair.
	3.	For heat protection, apply Verb’s Ghost Prep Heat Protectant to lightly coat the hair to seal while using heat tools.
	4.	Add shine with Verb’s Ghost Oil.
	5.	Finish off the look with Verb’s Volume Dry Texture Spray, focusing on the root and mid-lengths of the hair.
Final look - @leahhaywood cut and color by me giving those warm tones thanks @verbproducts for the hair love too…
